What shall I do?
There is a gentleman, my dear
    friend; and I fear not mine own shame as much as his peril.
I had rather than a thousand pound he were out of the
    house.
What shall I do?
I'll in, I'll in; follow your friend's counsel;
    I'll in.
PAGE]  I love thee and none but  
