Lady, as you are mine, I am yours.
I give away myself for you and dote upon the exchange.
Yea, my lord; I thank it, poor fool, it keeps on the windy
    side of care.
Thus goes every one to the world but
    I, and I am sunburnt.
I may sit in a corner and cry 'Heigh-ho for
